`MapDemeaner` accepts `fixef_tol` and `fixef_maxiter` arguments to control
convergence. `LsmrDemeaner` uses `fixef_atol` and `fixef_btol`; PyFixest passes
the larger of the two tolerances to the `within` and torch LSMR solvers for
compatibility with the older SciPy-style API.

::: {#e9030c26 .cell execution_count=3}
``` {.python .cell-code}
fit = pf.feols(
    "Y ~ X1 | f1",
    data=df,
    demeaner=MapDemeaner(backend="rust", fixef_tol=1e-10, fixef_maxiter=50_000),
)
```
:::
